Feature: Replace iOS-wide Global Variables with DataManagers

üßÝ Overview

The iOS app currently uses module-level global variables (declared at file scope,
outside any class) to share data between view controllers. These globals are
initialised once, mutated in place, and partially cleaned up in `deinit`.

This feature replaces them with typed, observable DataManager singletons backed
by Combine `@Published` properties so that any VC or SwiftUI view can subscribe
and react reactively ‚Äî without coupling to static state.

