‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
üéØ Goals
‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

1. Replace each global list/dictionary with a `@Published` property on a
   dedicated DataManager class (ObservableObject).
2. DataManagers are instantiated once and injected via `AppServices`
   (existing `HasAppServices` protocol pattern).
3. View controllers observe via Combine `sink`; SwiftUI views observe via
   `@ObservedObject` / `@EnvironmentObject`.
4. Preserve all current API call sites ‚Äî only the storage location changes.
5. Keep models (`MoviesData`, `SeatsData`, etc.) and their static fetch
   functions untouched; the static fns write into the DataManager instead
   of the bare global.
6. `deinit` cleanup moves from "removeAll on global" to "manager.reset()".
7. Mode flags (`adminPage`, `mapViewPage`, `adminUpdatePage`) are NOT in scope
   for this feature ‚Äî they are addressed in speckit.migration.specify.

