## DataManagers

REQ-DM-1: Create `SwiftLoginScreen/DataManagers/MoviesDataManager.swift`

  ```swift
  final class MoviesDataManager: ObservableObject {
      @Published var movies: [MoviesData] = []
      @Published var adminScreenings: [Admin_ScreenData] = []

      func reset() {
          movies.removeAll()
          adminScreenings.removeAll()
      }
  }
  ```

  Replaces: `TableData_` (‚Üí `movies`), `ScreenData_2` (‚Üí `adminScreenings`)

REQ-DM-2: Create `SwiftLoginScreen/DataManagers/VenuesDataManager.swift`

  ```swift
  final class VenuesDataManager: ObservableObject {
      @Published var venues: [PlacesData] = []
      @Published var filteredVenues: [PlacesData] = []   // was PlacesData2_

      func reset() {
          venues.removeAll()
          filteredVenues.removeAll()
      }
  }
  ```

  Replaces: `PlacesData_` (‚Üí `venues`), `PlacesData2_` (‚Üí `filteredVenues`)

REQ-DM-3: Create `SwiftLoginScreen/DataManagers/AdminDataManager.swift`

  ```swift
  final class AdminDataManager: ObservableObject {
      @Published var screenings: [ScreenData] = []

      func reset() {
          screenings.removeAll()
      }
  }
  ```

  Replaces: `ScreenData_` (‚Üí `screenings`)

REQ-DM-4: Create `SwiftLoginScreen/DataManagers/BasketDataManager.swift`

  ```swift
  final class BasketDataManager: ObservableObject {
      @Published var items: [Int: BasketData] = [:]
      @Published var seats: [SeatsData] = []
      @Published var tickets: [TicketsData] = []
      @Published var ticketMap: [String: String] = [:]   // was `tickets [String:String]`

      func reset() {
          items.removeAll()
          seats.removeAll()
          tickets.removeAll()
          ticketMap.removeAll()
      }
  }
  ```

  Replaces: `BasketData_` (‚Üí `items`), `SeatsData_` (‚Üí `seats`),
            `TicketsData_` (‚Üí `tickets`), `tickets` dict (‚Üí `ticketMap`)

REQ-DM-5: Register all DataManagers in `AppServices.swift`:

  ```swift
  let movies  = MoviesDataManager()
  let venues  = VenuesDataManager()
  let admin   = AdminDataManager()
  let basket  = BasketDataManager()
  ```

REQ-DM-6: All existing view controllers that use the old globals MUST be
  updated to access the manager via `appServices.*`:

  | Old global      | New access                                   |
  |-----------------|----------------------------------------------|
  | `TableData_`    | `appServices.movies.movies`                  |
  | `ScreenData_2`  | `appServices.movies.adminScreenings`         |
  | `ScreenData_`   | `appServices.admin.screenings`               |
  | `PlacesData_`   | `appServices.venues.venues`                  |
  | `PlacesData2_`  | `appServices.venues.filteredVenues`          |
  | `BasketData_`   | `appServices.basket.items`                   |
  | `SeatsData_`    | `appServices.basket.seats`                   |
  | `TicketsData_`  | `appServices.basket.tickets`                 |
  | `tickets`       | `appServices.basket.ticketMap`               |

REQ-DM-7: `SeatsData.addData(_:)` and `MoviesData.addData()` static functions
  MUST be updated to write into the DataManager instead of the bare global:

  ```swift
  // SeatsData.addData
  guard let app = UIApplication.shared.delegate as? AppDelegate else { return }
  app.services.basket.seats.removeAll()
  // ... append to app.services.basket.seats instead of SeatsData_
  ```

REQ-DM-8: `deinit` in each VC MUST call the manager's `reset()` method
  (or keep the list-specific `removeAll()` call on the manager property)
  instead of calling `removeAll()` on the bare global.

REQ-DM-9: The old bare global declarations MUST be deleted from their source
  files once all consumers are migrated. Remove in this order:
    1. `SeatsData_` / `TicketsData_` / `tickets` from PopOver.swift
    2. `BasketData_` from BasketVC.swift
    3. `PlacesData_` / `PlacesData2_` from MapViewController.swift
    4. `ScreenData_` from AdminVC.swift
    5. `TableData_` / `ScreenData_2` from MoviesVC.swift

REQ-DM-10: SwiftUI views (VenuesMigration) MUST be updated to read from
  `VenuesDataManager` via `@ObservedObject` / `@EnvironmentObject`:

  ```swift
  // Before (VenuesMigration.swift)
  PlacesData_.removeAll()
  PlacesData_.append(contentsOf: locations)

  // After
  @EnvironmentObject var venuesManager: VenuesDataManager
  venuesManager.venues = locations
  ```

‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
üîó Architecture Constraints
‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

- DataManagers live in `SwiftLoginScreen/DataManagers/` (new folder)
- Each DataManager is `final class` conforming to `ObservableObject`
- DataManagers are held by `AppServices` (not AppDelegate directly)
- UIKit VCs observe via `AnyCancellable` stored in `var cancellables = Set<AnyCancellable>()`
- SwiftUI views use `@ObservedObject` injected from the UIKit hosting controller
- No new third-party dependencies ‚Äî Combine only
- Models (`MoviesData`, `SeatsData`, `BasketData`, `TicketsData`, `PlacesData`,
  `ScreenData`, `Admin_ScreenData`) are NOT refactored in this ticket
- Static fetch functions on models (`MoviesData.addData()`, `SeatsData.addData()`)
  are preserved; only their write target changes
- `tickets [String:String]` dict in PopOver is renamed `ticketMap` in the manager
  to avoid collision with `TicketsData` array property name

