üìä Success Criteria (updated with API integration)
‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

- [ ] No bare global array/dictionary variables (suffix `_`) remain in the codebase
      except mode-flag booleans (out of scope)
- [ ] All four DataManagers exist under SwiftLoginScreen/DataManagers/
- [ ] AppServices holds and vends all four DataManagers
- [ ] All VC usages compile and reference manager properties via appServices
- [ ] SeatsData.addData() and MoviesData.addData() still work correctly
      (data appears in UI) after migrating write target to manager
- [ ] All API calls (mbooks.*, images.*, etc.) are routed through appServices
      and responses are written into the appropriate DataManager
- [ ] SwiftUI VenuesMigration reads from VenuesDataManager (no bare global)
- [ ] deinit blocks call manager.reset() instead of global.removeAll()
- [ ] Error handling is preserved; all errors logged with NSLog
- [ ] All @Published property writes occur on @MainActor
- [ ] No regression in: movies list, basket, seat selection, payment, admin flows,
      image loading, API error handling
